{"url": "https://www.allure.com/gallery/halloween-costumes-you-can-rewear", "text": "For a woman whose favorite holiday is Halloween, I am dreadfully unoriginal when it comes to costumes. I have been the same thing year after year for the entire span of my adult life: Marilyn Monroe in The Seven Year Itch. I blame the dress\u2014a vintage, silk number I dug out of my mom\u2019s old collection of resort season clothes back in high school. The dress ranks among all-time favorite things I\u2019ve ever worn\u2014so if I have to risk being a repeat-costume offender to get regular use out of it, so be it.\n\nThis season, it\u2019s time to up the ante a bit. Good riddance to the tarty (insert any occupation/animal/fruit here\u201d) get ups or the polyester bastardizations of Daenerys Targaryen\u2019s badass Game of Thrones outfits already hanging in the windows of every Halloween shop within a ten-mile radius. Spending your Halloween fund on long-term wardrobe pieces (both splurges and steals) is totally doable if you strategize your costume right. Try one of these fashion-inspired costumes\u2014all created with items you can wear again\u2014and your look will be a hit on All Hallows\u2019 Eve and beyond.", "images": ["https://media.allure.com/photos/57fd05dca1167e136e6efae3/1:1/w_320%2Cc_limit/HTRA202_VV213_H.JPG", "https://www.allure.com/verso/static/allure/assets/logo-reverse.7c3ec9af78d5f39e36d039cb1f9fef504150550e.svg", "https://media.allure.com/photos/57fbfdf1ef47698176bee817/16:9/w_2580,c_limit/halloweenlooksinspo.jpg", "https://media.allure.com/photos/57fd078fa1167e136e6efae5/1:1/w_320%2Cc_limit/marilyn%2520monroe.jpg", "https://media.allure.com/photos/57fbfae6ef47698176bee816/1:1/w_320%2Cc_limit/carriebradshaw.jpg", "https://media.allure.com/photos/57fbf724dd69c3d313b3e7d1/1:1/w_320%2Cc_limit/kendall%2520gigi.jpg", "https://media.allure.com/photos/57fbf722a1167e136e6efad7/1:1/w_320%2Cc_limit/holly%2520golightly.jpg", "https://media.allure.com/photos/57fbf723dd69c3